    "industrial_process_notes": "Not industrially polymerized -- biosynthesized in plants and harvested via wet milling: grinding, washing, and sieving to separate starch granules from other plant material (corn, potato, wheat, rice, cassava, and other crops), followed by drying. Enzymatic liquefaction (amylase) and saccharification convert starch into dextrins, maltose, and glucose syrups for many industrial uses.",
